				<figure><img src="https://expressionengine.com/asset/img/blog/5.0-announce-blog-news@2x_.png" alt="ExpressionEngine 5 has arrived"></figure>

<p>A momentous event in ExpressionEngine&#8217;s history has occurred. We just shipped Version 5, the first release as Free Open-Source Software!</p>

<p>A major version change gives a clean break and adds clarity for all users of what license they are running. This version removes licensing and Core feature restrictions, and has no impact on third-party add-ons.†</p>

<p>ExpressionEngine development is taking place in public <a href="https://github.com/ExpressionEngine/ExpressionEngine" title="" rel="external">on GitHub</a>, and licensed under a true open-source license: the permissive <a href="https://expressionengine.com/license">Apache 2.0 Software License</a>. We are thrilled at what this means for for the vast markets that must use open-source solutions. Earlier today, Rick Ellis <a href="https://expressionengine.com/blog/open-source-has-won">explained how we came to this decision</a>, and what it means for our future.</p>

<p>We’ve got a lot more to share in the coming days, but suffice it to say, we are pumped! We’ve changed who we are as a company overnight and the adrenaline is coursing! Make sure you check out our new first-party <a href="https://expressionengine.com/support">support options</a> and <a href="https://expressionengine.com/services">high-end services</a> that are now available. Companies that want to get involved as ExpressionEngine’s service providers can become <a href="https://expressionengine.com/partners">partners in our ecosystem</a>.</p>

<p>As always, this means the previous major version <a href="https://expressionengine.com/support/version-support">is now <em>legacy software</em></a>. Version 4, we barely got to know you. v4&#8217;s end of life is scheduled for November 16, 2019, and will now only receive security updates.</p>

<p>Lastly, ExpressionEngine has its own new account on Twitter, so make sure you <a href="https://twitter.com/intent/follow?screen_name=eecms" title="" rel="external">follow @eecms</a>!</p>

<p>† Due to this being a major version change all EEHarbor add-ons will <a href="https://eeharbor.com/blog/add-ons-for-expressionengine-5" title="" rel="external">need to be upgraded</a> <em>before</em> upgrading ExpressionEngine to ensure a smooth upgrade process.</p>

